trend_summary: Built-up area increases slowly, with most growth in eastern and southwest industrial parks and scattered housing infill around the central ring-road. Farmland in the north shows progressive reversion to woodland, raising overall vegetation cover. Core transport corridors stay unchanged, so pattern remains predominantly suburban of medium density.
notable_changes: Expansion of industrial/commercial blocks on the eastern edge
New warehouses and parking lots added southwest of the highway interchange
Denser residential infill inside the central circular road network
Several northern cropland parcels replaced by regenerating woodland
Minor extension to runway/apron area at north-west airfield
